        "id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2007_Solutions_2007s_page_001_6",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "by symmetry, Co is tangent to L there, so Cy and Cz are tangent. Writing a = 1/(2x + 1) in the first equation and substituting into the second, we must have",
        "bbox": [
          0.12593985550500433,
          0.312499999993333,
          0.49060151109241035,
